
1. Sudan is home to more pyramids than Egypt (100+).
2. It was once Africa’s largest country and  once represented over 8% of the whole African continent. 
That’s 2% of the world’s total land area. 
3. It was home to the legendary kingdom of Kush: an ancient African kingdom situated in what 
is now the Republic of Sudan.
4. It was once home to an under water research center.
5. Sudan fought Africa’s longest civil war; the Second Sudanese Civil War lasted 22 years.
